    <item>
      <title>Session 1</title>
      <link>https://janyljumadinova.com/highschool/session1/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 15 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://janyljumadinova.com/highschool/session1/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;session-1-your-first-interactive-web-page&#34;&gt;Session 1: Your First Interactive Web Page&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-you-will-build-today&#34;&gt;What You Will Build Today&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A web page with a button that changes color and text when you click it. Simple, but it introduces the &lt;strong&gt;three core technologies&lt;/strong&gt; of web development.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;your-demo-link-here&#34;&gt;See the finished example →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;setup&#34;&gt;Setup&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;option-a-codepen-recommended---works-in-browser&#34;&gt;Option A: CodePen (Recommended - Works in Browser)&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Go to &lt;a href=&#34;https://codepen.io/&#34;&gt;codepen.io&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Click &amp;quot;Start Coding&amp;quot; (no account needed to try it out)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;You will see three panels: HTML, CSS, and JS&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;We will use all three panels today&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;option-b-vs-code-local-installation&#34;&gt;Option B: VS Code (Local Installation)&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Download &lt;a href=&#34;https://code.visualstudio.com/&#34;&gt;VS Code&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Create a new folder: &lt;code&gt;gamecraft-session1&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Create a file: &lt;code&gt;index.html&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;html---the-structure&#34;&gt;HTML - The Structure&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;HTML is like the &lt;strong&gt;skeleton&lt;/strong&gt; of a web page. It defines what elements exist.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Session 2</title>
      <link>https://janyljumadinova.com/highschool/session2/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 15 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://janyljumadinova.com/highschool/session2/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;session-2-game-time---click-speed-and-gem-catcher&#34;&gt;Session 2: Game Time - Click Speed and Gem Catcher&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goal:&lt;/strong&gt; Set up VS Code and GitHub, then complete two games by adding the key logic yourself&#xA;&lt;strong&gt;Prerequisites:&lt;/strong&gt; Session 1 (HTML, CSS, JavaScript basics)&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-you-will-build-today&#34;&gt;What You Will Build Today&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You will start with &lt;strong&gt;starter code&lt;/strong&gt; that has the HTML, CSS, and structure already built. Your job is to fill in the &lt;strong&gt;game logic&lt;/strong&gt; — the JavaScript that makes the games actually work.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Session 2 Solution</title>
